'''Andrew Joseph Francis "Joe" Brown''' {{post-nominals|country=NZL|BEM|size=85%}} (3 October 1907 &ndash; 23 August 1986) was a New Zealand mechanic, entrepreneur, entertainment promoter, businessman and racehorse owner. He was born in [[Naseby, New Zealand|Naseby]], in the [[Maniototo]], [[New Zealand]] on 3 October 1907.<ref name="DNZB Brown">{{DNZB|title=Andrew Joseph Francis Brown|first= Jim|last= Sullivan|id=5b46|accessdate=23 April 2017}}</ref>

In the [[1970 New Year Honours]], Brown was awarded the [[British Empire Medal]] for services to the community as an entertainment promoter.<ref>{{London Gazette |issue=45001 |date=1 January 1970 |page=43 |supp=y }}</ref>

