The '''''Korea Economic Daily''''' (nicknamed '''''Hankyung''''' (from ''han'' - [[South Korea]] and ''kyung'' - business) is a newspaper published in [[South Korea]] that covers economic issues. It was founded in 1964 as the '''''Daily Economic Newspaper''''' and took its current name in 1980.<ref>[http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/snapshot.asp?privcapId=60940167 Company Overview of The Korea Economic Daily], ''[[Bloomberg Businessweek]]'' (accessed 2013-11-20).</ref>

