[[File:Stern of the Colombo Express.jpg|thumb|right|Goods being transported by [[container ship]].]] '''United Kingdom commercial law''' is the [[law]] which regulates the sale and purchase of goods and services, when doing business in the [[United Kingdom]].
==History== [[File:The Guildhall in the City of London - geograph.org.uk - 681581.jpg|thumb|right|The [[Guildhall, London]] was the administrative centre of London's medieval trade. Its most famous inhabitant, mythologised in the 19th century play, was [[Dick Whittington and His Cat]] who came when he heard that "[[London streets are paved with gold]]".]] *[[Lex Mercatoria]] *[[Hanseatic league]] *[[Guild]] *[[Mercantilism]] *[[Freedom of contract]] *''[[Laissez faire]]''
