{{Infobox person | name= Øystein Dahle | image=Dahle Schorre Holtermann.jpg | caption= Dahle (left) talking to Hans Jürgen Schorre and Harold Haltermann in 2003. | birth_date= {{birth date and age|1938|03|18|df=y}} | birth_place= [[Trondheim]], Norway | nationality= Norwegian | occupation= Businessperson and organizational leader | spouse= [[Nina Frisak]] | children= [[Gro Dahle]] }}
'''Øystein Dahle''' (born 18 March 1938) is a Norwegian businessperson and organizational leader.
He was born in [[Trondheim]]. He worked in [[Esso]] from 1963, and was vice president of [[Esso|Esso Norway]] from 1985 to 1995. He was the chairman of the [[Norwegian Trekking Association]] from 1994 to 2003, and in the [[Worldwatch Institute]] from 2002.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=2007|title=Øystein Dahle|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=Henriksen, Petter|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/%C3%98ystein_Dahle|language=Norwegian|accessdate=14 January 2010}}</ref> He is a fellow of the [[Norwegian Academy of Technological Sciences]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ntva.no/index.php?option=com_club&view=member&id=100%3Adahle-oystein&Itemid=60|title=Medlemmer: DAHLE, Øystein|publisher=[[Norwegian Academy of Technological Sciences]]|language=Norwegian|accessdate=29 November 2012}}</ref>
He is married to [[Nina Frisak]],<ref name=hvem>{{cite book |chapter=Frisak, Nina |title=Hvem er hvem? |last=Matlary |first=Janne Haaland |authorlink=Janne Haaland Matlary |year=2008 |editor=[[Knut Olav Åmås|Åmås, Knut Olav]] |publisher=Aschehoug |location=Oslo |isbn=978-82-03-23561-0 |language=Norwegian |page=164}}</ref> and is the father of [[Gro Dahle]].<ref>{{cite encyclopedia|year=2007|title=Gro Dahle|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=Henriksen, Petter|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/Gro_Dahle|language=Norwegian|accessdate=14 January 2010}}</ref>
